# Symptom-To-Cause Debugging

A lookup table from an observed symptom to the component most likely responsible and the first thing to check. Walk it top to bottom when a {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} surprises you. The components named here are the ones in `docs/concepts/core-concepts.md` section 3, so a diagnosis lands on a real row of the causal decomposition.

## 1. Symptom Table

The rows below are illustrative worked examples from different domains. Replace the components with this project's own, and add a row each time a new symptom is diagnosed.

| Symptom | Likely component | First check |
|---|---|---|
| All metrics worse at once (illustrative, ML) | Input preparation | Confirm normalization and input shape match the baseline; a single preprocessing change degrades everything downstream |
| Headline metric up but a counter-metric dropped (illustrative, ML) | Objective / criterion | Inspect failure-case panel; the objective likely traded the counter quantity for the headline |
| Effect appears only on some plates or batches (illustrative, wet-lab) | Sample handling | Plot the metric against plate or batch id; a position or lot effect mimics a real treatment effect |
| Average fine, tail metric spikes (illustrative, systems) | Request scheduler | Check the distribution overlay, not the mean; a batching or eviction change shows up only in the tail |

